      {
        "id": "travel-agent",
        "type": "anthropic.agents.ClaudeAgent",
        "data": {
          "prompt": "Plan an unforgettable 5-day trip to Tokyo, Japan.\n\nDeparting from San Francisco (SFO) around 2026-04-15, returning around 2026-04-20.\n2 adults, economy class, budget around $200/night for hotels.\n\nYour mission:\n1. Search for the best flights (try both nonstop and 1-stop options)\n2. Find highly-rated hotels in central Tokyo (Shinjuku, Shibuya, or Asakusa area)\n3. Discover local events and festivals happening during those dates\n4. Research top attractions, hidden gems, and food experiences\n5. Search for beautiful destination photos for visual inspiration\n\nWrite a COMPREHENSIVE travel brief that includes:\n- Flight comparison (top 3 options with prices, duration, airlines)\n- Hotel recommendations (top 3 with ratings, prices, location highlights)\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning/afternoon/evening activities\n- Local events and festivals during the visit\n- Must-try restaurants and food experiences\n- Practical tips (transport, etiquette, budget breakdown)\n- Hidden gems most tourists miss\n\nMake it exciting and inspirational — this should feel like opening a premium travel magazine.",
          "model": {
            "type": "language_model",
            "provider": "anthropic",
            "id": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
            "name": "Claude Sonnet 4.6"
          },
          "system_prompt": "You are an elite travel concierge with deep knowledge of destinations worldwide. You have access to flight search, hotel search, event discovery, web search, and image search tools.\n\nYour approach:\n1. Start by searching flights to establish logistics\n2. Search hotels in the best neighborhoods\n3. Discover events happening during the travel dates\n4. Research attractions, restaurants, and hidden gems via web search\n5. Find inspiring destination photos\n\nWrite with the passion of a travel writer and the precision of a logistics planner. Use real data from your searches. Format the brief beautifully with clear sections, bullet points, and practical details. Include specific prices, ratings, and links where available.\n\nEnd your brief with a one-line poetic summary of the destination that captures its essence — this will be used to generate a travel poster.",
          "max_turns": 20,
          "allowed_tools": [],
          "permission_mode": "acceptEdits",
          "use_claude_credentials": true
        },
        "ui_properties": {
          "position": {
